<subSubSection id="C30198A6FFF5FFCDFF02FF44FCE27759" pageId="9" pageNumber="122" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF5FFCDFF02FF44FF257598" blockId="9.[130,776,216,561]" box="[132,207,216,242]" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF5FFCDFF02FF64FCE27759" blockId="9.[130,776,216,561]" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFF5FFCDFF02FF64FE81747A" author="LECOMTE H." box="[132,363,248,274]" pageId="9" pageNumber="122" pagination="915 - 978" refId="ref13275" refString="LECOMTE H. 1930. - Ebenacees, in LECOMTE H. &amp; HUMBERT H. (eds), Flore generale de l'Indo-Chine. Vol. 3. Masson &amp; Co., Paris: 915 - 978. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 27563332" type="book chapter" year="1930">Lecomte (1930: 948)</bibRefCitation>
only cited a 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF5FFCDFE71FF64FDB0747A" box="[503,602,248,274]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">Chevalier</emphasis>
collection from “ 
<collectingCountry id="F30C8BBDFFF5FFCDFF08FE84FF0B745A" box="[142,225,280,306]" name="Vietnam" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">Annam</collectingCountry>
: S. massif de Hon-ba, alt. 
<quantity id="4CE366C8FFF5FFCDFE7CFE8BFD70745A" box="[506,666,279,306]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="122" unit="m" value="1350.0" valueMax="1500.0" valueMin="1200.0">1200–1500 m</quantity>
., en forêt” as the original material. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFF5FFCDFE0BFEA4FDB5743A" author="NGUYEN T. H." box="[397,607,311,338]" pageId="9" pageNumber="122" pagination="63 - 74" refId="ref13500" refString="NGUYEN T. H. 1996. - Fam. Ebenaceae Gurke, in AVERYANOV L. V., NGUYEN T. B., NGUYEN T. H., PHAN K. L., SEROV V. P. &amp; AKIMOVA G. A. (eds), Vascular Plants Synopsis of Vietnamese Flora. Russian Academy of Sciences, Saint Petersburg, Russia and National Center for Natural Sciences and Technology of Vietnam: 63 - 74." type="book chapter" year="1996">Nguyen (1996: 66)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF5FFCDFD23FEABFF427419" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">Chevalier s.n.</emphasis>
(P) as the 
<typeStatus id="54A0758FFFF5FFCDFE9AFECBFE947419" box="[284,382,343,369]" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">holotype</typeStatus>
, effectively making a first-step lectotypification. We have located five sheets of 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF5FFCDFDD1FEEBFCED74F9" box="[599,775,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">Chevalier 38854</emphasis>
at E, K and P, collected from the cited locality, and annotated by Chevalier as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BB0AEFFF5FFCDFEB2FE24FDB274B9" authority="A. Chev." authorityName="A. Chev." box="[308,600,439,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="9" pageNumber="122" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fleuryana">
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF5FFCDFEB2FE24FE1074B9" box="[308,506,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">Diospyros fleuryana</emphasis>
A.Chev.
</taxonomicName>
”. Three of them, K000342277, P00721602 andP00721604 are also annotated as “type” in Chevalier’s handwriting.The specimen P00721602, being in the best conditions, is chosen here as the 
<typeStatus id="54A0758FFFF5FFCDFD18FD8BFCE97759" box="[670,771,535,561]" pageId="9" pageNumber="122">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
